Pre-Game Insights: Denmark returned to Parken for another UEFA Nations League home clash against Serbia.
Both teams are under new management after their exits from Euro 2024.
Denmark is under caretaker charge with Lars Knudsen, while Serbia remains with Dragan Stojkovic.
Denmark won 2-0 against Switzerland, while Serbia drew 0-0 with Spain.
Denmark have won 11 of their last 12 home matches, with a draw against Switzerland in March.
Serbia needs to improve, having won just two of their last 10 matches and narrowly progressing in Euro 2024.
